text: SPOILER ALERT: This post contains details on Big Brother Season 26, Episode 37, which aired on Thursday, October 10. The final and most crucial eviction of Big Brother Season 26 will be decided by the houseguest who wins the Power of Veto. The four remaining houseguests are Cam Sullivan-Brown, Chelsie Baham, Makensy Manbeck, and Rubina Bernabe. Chelsie already secured her spot in the Final 3 by winning the Head of Household competition, her fourth win of the season. As HOH, Chelsie put Cam and Makensy on the block to face eviction. Who won the Power of Veto in Big Brother Season 26, Week 12? Watch on Deadline At the POV competition, Rubina and Chelsie were quickly eliminated, leaving Cam and Makensy to compete head-to-head to remain in the game. In the end, Makensy won the POV, had the opportunity to save herself from eviction, and cast the one and only sending another housemate to the Jury. Who was up for eviction on Big Brother Season 26, Week 12? Makensy used the veto on herself and Rubina went on the block as she was the only option for replacement. RELATED: ‘Big Brother’ Season 26 Cast Photos How did the Big Brother Season 26 house vote in Week 12? Makensy had the only vote and voted for Rubina. Who was evicted from Big Brother Season 26 in Week 12? Rubina was the thirteenth houseguest evicted from the Big Brother house. Who will decide the Big Brother Season 26 winner? The evicted houseguests that are now part of the Jury House will determine the winner of Big Brother Season 26 which includes Quinn, T’kor, Leah, Angela, Kimo, and Rubina. One final houseguest will join the jury on finale night, to crown the winner of the season.
html:
SPOILER ALERT: This post contains details on Big Brother Season 26, Episode 37, which aired on Thursday, October 10.

The final and most crucial eviction of Big Brother Season 26 will be decided by the houseguest who wins the Power of Veto.

The four remaining houseguests are Cam Sullivan-Brown, Chelsie Baham, Makensy Manbeck, and Rubina Bernabe.

Chelsie already secured her spot in the Final 3 by winning the Head of Household competition, her fourth win of the season. As HOH, Chelsie put Cam and Makensy on the block to face eviction.

Who won the Power of Veto in Big Brother Season 26, Week 12?

Watch on Deadline

At the POV competition, Rubina and Chelsie were quickly eliminated, leaving Cam and Makensy to compete head-to-head to remain in the game. In the end, Makensy won the POV, had the opportunity to save herself from eviction, and cast the one and only sending another housemate to the Jury.

Who was up for eviction on Big Brother Season 26, Week 12?

Makensy used the veto on herself and Rubina went on the block as she was the only option for replacement.

RELATED: ‘Big Brother’ Season 26 Cast Photos

How did the Big Brother Season 26 house vote in Week 12?

Makensy had the only vote and voted for Rubina.

Who was evicted from Big Brother Season 26 in Week 12?

Rubina was the thirteenth houseguest evicted from the Big Brother house.

Who will decide the Big Brother Season 26 winner?

The evicted houseguests that are now part of the Jury House will determine the winner of Big Brother Season 26 which includes Quinn, T’kor, Leah, Angela, Kimo, and Rubina.

One final houseguest will join the jury on finale night, to crown the winner of the season.
